{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.74",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 74,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 74 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:1",
      "text": "O God, why dost thou cast us off for ever? Why does thy anger smoke against the sheep of thy pasture?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:2",
      "text": "Remember thy congregation, which thou hast gotten of old, which thou hast redeemed to be the tribe of thy heritage! Remember Mount Zion, where thou hast dwelt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:3",
      "text": "Direct thy steps to the perpetual ruins; the enemy has destroyed everything in the sanctuary!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:4",
      "text": "Thy foes have roared in the midst of thy holy place; they set up their own signs for signs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:5",
      "text": "At the upper entrance they hacked the wooden trellis with axes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:6",
      "text": "And then all its carved wood they broke down with hatchets and hammers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:7",
      "text": "They set thy sanctuary on fire; to the ground they desecrated the dwelling place of thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:8",
      "text": "They said to themselves, “We will utterly subdue them”; they burned all the meeting places of God in the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:9",
      "text": "We do not see our signs; there is no longer any prophet, and there is none among us who knows how long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:10",
      "text": "How long, O God, is the foe to scoff? Is the enemy to revile thy name for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:11",
      "text": "Why dost thou hold back thy hand, why dost thou keep thy right hand in thy bosom?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:12",
      "text": "Yet God my King is from of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:13",
      "text": "Thou didst divide the sea by thy might; thou didst break the heads of the dragons on the waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:14",
      "text": "Thou didst crush the heads of Leviathan, thou didst give him as food for the creatures of the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:15",
      "text": "Thou didst cleave open springs and brooks; thou didst dry up ever-flowing streams.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:16",
      "text": "Thine is the day, thine also the night; thou hast established the luminaries and the sun.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:17",
      "text": "Thou hast fixed all the bounds of the earth; thou hast made summer and winter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:18",
      "text": "Remember this, O Lord, how the enemy scoffs, and an impious people reviles thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:19",
      "text": "Do not deliver the soul of thy dove to the wild beasts; do not forget the life of thy poor for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:20",
      "text": "Have regard for thy covenant; for the dark places of the land are full of the habitations of violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:21",
      "text": "Let not the downtrodden be put to shame; let the poor and needy praise thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:22",
      "text": "Arise, O God, plead thy cause; remember how the impious scoff at thee all the day!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.74.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:23",
      "text": "Do not forget the clamor of thy foes, the uproar of thy adversaries which goes up continually!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
